From: Brian Telfer <britel@microsoft.com>
Subject: [PATCH] dnf: Pass --setopt=logdir=/tmp during info queries

dnf unconditionally opens /var/log/dnf.log for writing during info
operations. After MIC partition resize, the image rootfs is remounted
read-only, so the dnf info call fails with:
    Cannot open log file: (30) - Read-only file system [/var/log/dnf5.log]
which makes IsPackageInstalled return false for all queries, breaking
bootloader detection on AZL4 base images.

This is the same one-line fix already present in Vince Perri's
user/vinceaperri/azl4-support branch (microsoft/azurelinux-image-tools
PR #698). Carried as a Trident-side patch on top of the pinned
multi-distro-grub commit (9b7f9806b) until PR #698 lands and
propagates into multi-distro-grub.

Drop this patch the moment the pinned MIC SHA in PINNED.md is bumped
past Vince's fix.

Co-authored-by: Vince Perri <vinceaperri@users.noreply.github.com>

---
 toolkit/tools/pkg/imagecustomizerlib/packagemanager_dnf.go | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/toolkit/tools/pkg/imagecustomizerlib/packagemanager_dnf.go b/toolkit/tools/pkg/imagecustomizerlib/packagemanager_dnf.go
index 5a8e2c1..b1f7e4a 100644
--- a/toolkit/tools/pkg/imagecustomizerlib/packagemanager_dnf.go
+++ b/toolkit/tools/pkg/imagecustomizerlib/packagemanager_dnf.go
@@ -183,7 +183,9 @@ func (pm *dnfPackageManager) createOutputCallback() func(string) {
 }
 
 func (pm *dnfPackageManager) isPackageInstalled(imageChroot safechroot.ChrootInterface, packageName string) bool {
-	err := shell.NewExecBuilder("dnf", "info", "--installed", packageName).
+	// dnf unconditionally opens /var/log/dnf.log for writing during info operations, so set logdir to a location we
+	// know is always writable, even in read-only chroots.
+	err := shell.NewExecBuilder("dnf", "info", "--setopt=logdir=/tmp", "--installed", packageName).
 		LogLevel(logrus.TraceLevel, logrus.DebugLevel).
 		Chroot(imageChroot.ChrootDir()).
 		Execute()
-- 
